partial_orders.reason: Both edits remove the exact same import statement 'import collections' from different files. This represents a bulk/pattern synchronization where identical textual substitutions (removing 'import collections') are being applied to the same type of syntactic construct (import statements) across multiple files. This appears to be part of a single, contiguous refactor to remove unused collections imports. Since both edits perform the identical before→after pattern (collections import → no collections import) on the same construct type, and either edit can be staged first as part of this cleanup operation, this qualifies as bi-directional neighbours.
